    "plain_content":  "View in browser ( {{Weblink}} )\n\n*December 2020*\n\n*Creative Ideas for*\n*Traveling Designers.*\n\n*by Jolie Kingston*\n*Principle Product Designer, LivingType*\n\n*As a remote designer, it can be a challenge to collaborate with your team. Even though technology makes up for it 90% of the way, there\u0027s still that 10%. Body language, tone, water-cooler conversations. You miss the in-between moments that help you understand what someone is looking for and why. Fortunately, I\u0027ve learned a handful of strategies to bridge the gap and get the inside scoop so you can do your best work no matter where you\u0027re working.*\n\nSee The Tips\n\n*\"Design is not just what it looks like and feels like. Design is how it works.\"*\n*- Steve Jobs, co-founder of Apple, Inc.*\n\n*Read More Stories\n*\n*Designing with a Distributed Team* ( http:// )\n*How to Involve Stakeholders in your Design Process* ( http:// )\n*Intelligent Accessibility on the World Wide Web* ( http:// )\n\nMore Stories Online\n\n{{Sender_Name}}\n\n{{Sender_Address}} , {{Sender_City}} , {{Sender_State}} {{Sender_Zip}}\n\nUnsubscribe ( {{{unsubscribe}}} ) - Unsubscribe Preferences ( {{{unsubscribe_preferences}}} )\n\n♥ POWERED BY TWILIO SENDGRID ( https://sendgrid.com/ )",
